<HEADLINE>
FT  12 OCT 94 / World Trade News: Land Rovers in South Africa
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN GRIFFITHS
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LONDON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The UK's Rover Group is to assemble Land Rover four-wheel-drive vehicles in
South Africa, at a car plant operated at Rosslyn, near Pretoria, by Rover's
parent company, BMW. The venture, in which Rover Group itself is investing
Pounds 10m, represents one of the first visible benefits arising from
Rover's purchase by the German luxury carmaker earlier this year for Pounds
800m.
It will also mark Land Rover's return to South Africa as an assembler for
the first time since it sold a smaller assembly operation in Capetown to
local entrepreneurs in the mid-1980s.
</TEXT>
