<HEADLINE>
FT  11 OCT 94 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Tea Broker's Association reports less demand. A few selected best Assams
sold well at firm rates but others were 2 to 5 easier following quality,
with plainest sorts neglected. Brightest East Africans sold readily at last
levels but below best lost 4 to 8 pence. Mediums opened about steady but
closed up to 5 down. Bright ceylons sold well at firm rates but plainer
sorts were lower. Fair demand at about steady rates although Ugandas were
neglected. Quotations: best available 200p/kg., good 140p/kg., good medium
126p/kg., medium 115p/kg., low medium 86p/kg. nom. The highest price
realised this week was 230p for an Assam pf.
</TEXT>
