<HEADLINE>
FT  11 OCT 94 / International Capital Markets: Nordbanken to absorb parts of
Carnegie unit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Nordbanken, the Swedish state-owned bank, has decided to increase
significantly its services in money and bond markets to both Swedish and
international customers, Reuter reports from Stockholm.
'This will happen by taking over the Swedish money and bond market
operations in brokerage Carnegie,' the bank said.
However, it made no comment about what would happen to Carnegie's other
operations, including its equity brokerage. Carnegie is currently a
wholly-owned subsidiary of Nordbanken.
Earlier this year, Nordbanken said its goal was to spread the ownership of
Carnegie. It is not clear how this policy will be affected by the latest
move.
In March, Westdeutsche Landesbank Girozentrale pulled out of talks to buy
Carnegie.
