   By ANDREW BOLGER
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Dorling Kindersley Holdings, the publisher of illustrated reference books
and multimedia products, is to create CD-Rom versions of the best-selling
Chronicle publications from Bertelsmann, the German-based media group.
The UK group has acquired rights to publish the Chronicle titles as books in
the UK and US and in CD-Rom form worldwide.
