<HEADLINE>
FT  11 OCT 94 / Observer: Not tonight
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sexual politics are taking on a new meaning in the run-up to Germany's
elections. According to the German version of Playboy magazine, there is a
strong correlation between voting and mating habits. Polling some 1,300
people, the mag discovered that more than 50 per cent of Christian Democrat
voters record having sex once a month or less. Germany's most sexually
active voters are to be found in the reformed communist Party of Democratic
Socialism; 20 per cent reckon they have sex at least once a day. Is that why
they have no chance of forming the next government?
</TEXT>
