<HEADLINE>
FT  11 OCT 94 / Observer: Stepping out
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A new star is about to take her bow in London's diplomatic round. Noemi
Sanin, Colombia's new ambassador, is a conservative politician from Medelln
who enlivened many a dreary Latin American summit in her last job as
Colombia's foreign minister.
The London posting, which she will take up after completing a course in
English, is seen by some as just a stepping stone to her ultimate goal of
becoming Colombia's president. So as well as being out to refurbish her
country's image as a land of drug traffickers, she will be keen to have lots
of interesting photo-opportunities beamed back to Bogota as evidence of her
statesmanship.
No doubt Tristan Garel-Jones, the former foreign office minister and ardent
admirer of Ms Sanin and her country, can be counted on to make the right
introductions.
</TEXT>
