FT  11 OCT 94 / London's economy set for slow growth
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
London's economy is expected to grow 3 per cent in 1994 and 2.8 per cent in
1995, slower than the UK average, according to the London Chamber of
Commerce and Industry.
The chamber says the recession hit the London economy particularly hard
because of its exposure to the service sector but also because of a further
erosion of its manufacturing base.
London now has an unemployment rate higher than all other regions bar the
north of England and Northern Ireland.
The chamber says the housing market is a weak link, with London having the
worst negative equity position in the country.
