<HEADLINE>
FT  11 OCT 94 / Nuclear safety breach claimed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Safety regulations have been breached at Drigg, the repository for low-level
nuclear waste at Sellafield in Cumbria, according to Greenpeace.
The environmental group said a team entered the dump one night in July and
found evidence suggesting that it contained intermediate level waste. The
waste was uncovered, and contained jagged edges which could tear the
membrane which isolates it from the water supply.
British Nuclear Fuels, which operates the site, said it had been running the
site for 35 years to the complete satisfaction of the authorising bodies.
